OL,3,CExecutive has agreed #55m in new
OL,4,Cfunding allocations
OL,6,FIn terms of capital spending
OL,7,Fallocations, Mr O'Dowd said almost
OL,8,F#17million will be invested in the
OL,9,Ftransport and roads network, including
OL,10,Ffunding for fixing roads.
OL,12,FThere will be #6.5million "to help
OL,13,Fpeople with disabilities adapt their
OL,14,Fhomes ` ensuring their living spaces
OL,15,Ftruly meet their needs and support
OL,16,Fgreater independence".
OL,18,FHe added that #6.4million will be
OL,19,Fallocated for education.
